# Agent Spawning

## TR-AGT-003 — Agentic node loop contracts

Every agent pipeline node declares input schema, output schema, exit condition, and resource budget before implementation. Nodes exposed as MCP tools additionally declare four tool annotation hints (readOnlyHint, destructiveHint, idempotentHint, openWorldHint) describing blast radius — required only for MCP-exposed nodes.

## TR-AGT-002 — Deterministic operations use scripts not agents

Operations that require repeatable results should be implemented in scripts, code, queries, tests, or validators. Agents may call those deterministic tools, but should not replace them.

## TR-AGT-004 — Agent trigger type classified at design time

Each agent invocation is classified as event-driven, scheduled, or user-initiated. Undocumented triggers are non-compliant unmanaged side effects.

## TR-AGT-005 — Behavioral mode declaration

A behavioral mode is a named, trigger-activated instruction set that changes how an agent approaches a task, orthogonal to process-intensity gate strictness. Each mode declares a trigger, activated behavior, exit condition, and precedence (safety and process-intensity rules always win on conflict).
